str2: Melchizedek, king and priest of Salem. Of Hebrew origin; Melchisedek, a patriarch.
A king, ruler, but in some passages clearly to be translated: emperor. Probably from basis; a sovereign.
Salem, doubtless identical with Jerusalem. Of Hebrew origin; Salem, a place in Palestine.
A priest, one who offers sacrifice to a god (in Jewish and pagan religions; of Christians only met.). From hieros; a priest.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
Highest, most high, the heights. Superlative from the base of hupsos; highest, i.e. the Supreme, or the heavens.

str2: To meet, encounter, fall in with. From sun and a derivative of anti; to meet with; figuratively, to occur.
Abraham, progenitor of the Hebrew race. Of Hebrew origin; Abraham, the Hebrew patriarch.

str2: To turn back, return. From hupo and strepho; to turn under, i.e. To return.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Slaughter, smiting in battle. From kopto; cutting, i.e. Carnage.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.

str2: (lit: I speak well of) I bless; pass: I am blessed. From a compound of eu and logos; to speak well of, i.e. to bless.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
